    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin <date value="1916-09-03">Sept 3rd [1916]</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-09-03">Sept 3rd [1916]</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Marcelle:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            I’ve had a great
            time with those little books
            you so kindly sent me.  The
            one by Cobb is great.  I laughed 
            so hard the inmates thought
            there had been a mistake and
            that I should have been sent
            to <unclear>Chardendou [sp?]</unclear>.
            </p><p>
            This afternoon I am
            to dress and go to the concert.
            The program is excellent &mdash; really
            excellent, and for the first time
            I’ll hear the Rumanian National
            anthem.  Faust is also to be sung.
            Lasts from 2 ‘till 6.
            </p><p>
            As you probably know
            the escadrille is leaving Bar.  Don’t
            know where its going but on the
            way will have two days in 
            Paris.  Just my luck.
            </p><p>
            Now I am overwhelmed
            with books and magazines.  Every
            mail has been unloading them on
            me and men in the depot have
            given me a big supply.  Have
            
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            just finished Train 8.47.  Ever
            read it?  If not don’t ask
            you father what it is.  Very
            amusing, tho [sic].
            </p><p>
            You’re a very fine girl
            Marcelle, I’ve just been thinking
            you over as I lay here in
            bed.  Too serious sometimes &mdash;
            with a young girl’s illusion about
            romance, but nevertheless &mdash;
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>My best to you.</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim.</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            P.S.  My you should see the
            letter I got from Yvonne &mdash; very
            friendly.  Calls me a grand garcon
            bien sage.  Maybe I’ll cut out
            the embusque yet.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
            <!-- [With this letter is an envelope addressed to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin, 148 Bis Rue de Longchamp, 
            	XVI, Paris.  The post mark appears to read, “TRESOR ET FDSSES”.] -->
            
           </div1>
